data.chText: 离开市中心；在（或向）市郊
data.enText: in or to the parts of a town or city that are away from the centre, where people live

data.chText: 他们住在市郊的一套公寓。
data.enText: They live in an apartment uptown.

data.chText: 我们向市郊走了好几条街才找到一辆出租车。
data.enText: We walked uptown a couple of blocks until we found a cab.

data.chText: 在（或向）市郊住宅区的；市郊住宅区的
data.enText: in, to or typical of the parts of a town or city that are away from the centre, where people live

data.chText: 开往市郊住宅区的火车

data.enText: typical of an area of a town or city where people have a lot of money

tr: a residential part of town away from the central commercial district
of or located in the upper part of a town
toward or in the upper part of town

value.def: If you go uptown, or go to a place uptown, you go away from the centre of a town or city towards the edge. Uptown sometimes refers to a part of the city other than the main business district.

example.ex: He rode uptown and made his way to Bob's apartment...
example.tran: 他乘车前往城外鲍勃的公寓。

value.tran: 往(或在)城外;往(或在)城镇的非商业区
